1
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:04,590
Bhrugen: What is dependency injection?

2
00:00:04,590 --> 00:00:06,870
It is a common interview question,

3
00:00:06,870 --> 00:00:10,590
and explaining that with a real world example will show

4
00:00:10,590 --> 00:00:13,830
that you really understand the concept.

5
00:00:13,830 --> 00:00:17,820
My name is Bhrugen and welcome to Dot Net Mastery.

6
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:21,960
If you enjoy free content related to .NET programming,

7
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:24,690
make sure to subscribe to the channel.

8
00:00:24,690 --> 00:00:29,460
That way you will be notified when new content is uploaded.

9
00:00:29,460 --> 00:00:31,290
Now, back to the main question,

10
00:00:31,290 --> 00:00:34,470
what exactly is dependency injection?

11
00:00:34,470 --> 00:00:38,700
Dependency injection is a design pattern in which a class

12
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:43,290
or object has its dependent classes injected

13
00:00:43,290 --> 00:00:45,573
rather than directly creating them.

14
00:00:46,650 --> 00:00:50,100
This is done so that we do not have to create, manage,

15
00:00:50,100 --> 00:00:51,900
and dispose the object,

16
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:55,413
and it improves the loose coupling between classes.

17
00:00:56,610 --> 00:00:58,800
Now, that is too much technical.

18
00:00:58,800 --> 00:00:59,910
Do not worry.

19
00:00:59,910 --> 00:01:03,480
Let me simplify that with a real world example

20
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:06,243
that almost everyone can relate to.

21
00:01:07,260 --> 00:01:11,760
In this example, we have Bob here who wants to go on hiking.

22
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:13,380
Now, it is a long hike,

23
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:16,380
and for that he will require many supplies

24
00:01:16,380 --> 00:01:19,410
like maps, flashlight, protein bars,

25
00:01:19,410 --> 00:01:21,120
and much more.

26
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:24,360
So he places all of them in his backpack,

27
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:27,240
and next day when he goes on the hiking,

28
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:30,000
he takes the backpack with him.

29
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,420
The bag that he has acts as an container

30
00:01:33,420 --> 00:01:36,030
so during the hike when he needs anything,

31
00:01:36,030 --> 00:01:39,273
he can take it out of the container and use them.

32
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:42,150
This is the simple concept.

33
00:01:42,150 --> 00:01:45,090
You put the items that you need in a container

34
00:01:45,090 --> 00:01:46,380
and when you need them,

35
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:48,960
they are already present in the container

36
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:52,143
so you can directly fetch them from the container.

37
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:56,250
Now, that is a little too easy to understand,

38
00:01:56,250 --> 00:01:59,610
but how does it relate to programming world?

39
00:01:59,610 --> 00:02:01,710
To show that, let me elaborate

40
00:02:01,710 --> 00:02:04,743
a situation without dependency injection.

41
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:08,520
In our application, we have three pages,

42
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:12,600
and we have some common functionality that we want to use

43
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:15,480
across all the three pages,

44
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,640
like we want to send emails

45
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:20,280
and we want to access our database

46
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:23,280
in all the three pages that we have.

47
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:27,240
So first, let's say we have to access database.

48
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,770
In order to do that,

49
00:02:28,770 --> 00:02:32,640
what we typically do is create object of our class,

50
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:35,670
which is used to access the database.

51
00:02:35,670 --> 00:02:39,090
Let me call that DB for this example.

52
00:02:39,090 --> 00:02:42,420
Then we might call some method inside that object

53
00:02:42,420 --> 00:02:44,070
and retrieve data.

54
00:02:44,070 --> 00:02:45,390
Once we are done,

55
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:48,663
we will be disposing that object that was created.

56
00:02:49,590 --> 00:02:52,650
This object creation logic we will have to write

57
00:02:52,650 --> 00:02:54,630
in all the three pages

58
00:02:54,630 --> 00:02:58,710
and same thing we will have to do with email, as well.

59
00:02:58,710 --> 00:03:01,710
By doing that, we are actually solving the issue

60
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:05,730
of having email and database access in our page.

61
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:07,380
But as you can see,

62
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:12,240
we have a lot of duplicate code that is being written here,

63
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:16,770
and when we design, we try to build the perfect solution.

64
00:03:16,770 --> 00:03:19,500
But sadly, most of the time we do not know

65
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,620
the complete future of a project.

66
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:25,440
It could very well happen that in future,

67
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:27,360
because of some reason,

68
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:31,530
you might have to create a new class for sending email

69
00:03:31,530 --> 00:03:34,920
or maybe a new data access class.

70
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:37,440
What happens in that case?

71
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,720
Well, it is simple for now.

72
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,720
In all the pages where we had the old object,

73
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:45,210
we will replace that with the new class.

74
00:03:45,210 --> 00:03:49,080
Like in this case we have Db_new class

75
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:50,180
and we have Email_new.

76
00:03:52,410 --> 00:03:54,180
And when we think about that,

77
00:03:54,180 --> 00:03:57,000
it does not seem like a big issue.

78
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,480
That is because we only have three pages right now.

79
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:05,480
But what if your application had 30 pages or 300 pages?

80
00:04:05,790 --> 00:04:08,880
You will have to modify that in all the pages

81
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:11,070
and on top of that you will be dealing with

82
00:04:11,070 --> 00:04:13,470
creating the object, managing,

83
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:14,853
and disposing them.

84
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:18,300
That is a time-consuming effort

85
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:21,093
when we have to do that in all the pages.

86
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:25,440
So what is the solution to avoid all of this

87
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:28,620
and get an optimal architecture?

88
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:31,833
The answer to that is dependency injection.

89
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:36,780
Let me show you how the same situation would look like

90
00:04:36,780 --> 00:04:39,420
with dependency injection.

91
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:41,820
Again, we would have the three pages

92
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:45,630
and we would have email and database functionality.

93
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:49,680
These are common things that we had before, as well,

94
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,470
but right now we would have something special,

95
00:04:52,470 --> 00:04:56,190
which is a dependency injection container,

96
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:59,460
and in that container we will register both email

97
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:01,380
and database service.

98
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:06,060
So there we will have an interface for IEmail and IDb

99
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:09,390
and we will have the implementation inside email

100
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:10,713
and DB class.

101
00:05:11,670 --> 00:05:15,270
When any page would access these functionalities,

102
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:20,270
they would ask for an implementation of IDb or IEmail.

103
00:05:20,790 --> 00:05:23,430
The pages do not know what implementation

104
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:25,260
will be given to them.

105
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:28,350
Dependency injection container is responsible

106
00:05:28,350 --> 00:05:29,553
for all of that.

107
00:05:30,510 --> 00:05:33,660
So what the framework will do is when a page request

108
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:36,780
implementation of email interface,

109
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:39,000
it will look in the container to find out

110
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:44,000
that email interface is implemented inside the email class,

111
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:47,460
so it will automatically create the object

112
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:49,860
and pass it on to the page.

113
00:05:49,860 --> 00:05:51,810
That way we do not have to deal with

114
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:54,120
creating object, disposing,

115
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,313
or managing that in our page.

116
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,430
Pages will look very clean

117
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:01,890
because they will just have the interface

118
00:06:01,890 --> 00:06:03,990
and implementation is provided

119
00:06:03,990 --> 00:06:06,513
by the dependency injection container.

120
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:09,060
The best thing is in future,

121
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:12,420
if you have to change or replace the implementation,

122
00:06:12,420 --> 00:06:15,270
you do not have to do in all the places

123
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:17,910
because you only registered the implementation

124
00:06:17,910 --> 00:06:19,410
in the container,

125
00:06:19,410 --> 00:06:22,230
so only in that file you will have to go

126
00:06:22,230 --> 00:06:24,813
and replace with the new implementation.

127
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,570
So our DB and email,

128
00:06:27,570 --> 00:06:31,650
we just need to replace them with DB new and email new

129
00:06:31,650 --> 00:06:34,170
and all the pages will automatically get

130
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:35,943
the new implementation.

131
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,970
So with that, you can see email

132
00:06:38,970 --> 00:06:43,120
and database are now loosely coupled with the other classes

133
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:48,090
and that is the beauty of dependency injection.

134
00:06:48,090 --> 00:06:50,640
Now, dependency injection is built in

135
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:53,460
if you are using .NET framework,

136
00:06:53,460 --> 00:06:56,100
so you just have to register the service

137
00:06:56,100 --> 00:07:00,270
and .NET framework will take care of everything else.

138
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:04,470
I hope with that short video you have a better understanding

139
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:06,870
of dependency injection.

140
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:08,670
If you enjoyed the video,

141
00:07:08,670 --> 00:07:10,650
make sure to like the video

142
00:07:10,650 --> 00:07:14,280
and leave a comment if you have any other question

143
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:17,580
or topics that I should cover next.

144
